name: Agnelli sacrificali
The Gorgeous Georgians Heroes and Villains
The Vile Victorians Crime and Punishment
The Groovy Greeks: Alexander The Not-So-Great

volume.name: No Need for Tenchi! Part Eight

description:
Mo Manna Mo Problems!

Manna. Energy source of the dead. For AFTERLIFE INC. there is no greater resource in their ongoing mission to modernise the hereafter. But when CEO Jack Fortune attempts to revolutionise the manna industry, little could he have anticipated the horror his actions would unleash.

Dark forces - and darker appetites - have set their sights on Jack's dreams for the future. Faced with a hunger that threatens to consume their entire world, can AFTERLIFE INC. survive the coming harvest... or will even the dead have cause to fear the reaper?
name: Lifeblood

description: Albert the Alien is just a normal everyday kid...from the stars! On his first day in school on Earth, Albert has to make new friends, avoid the school bully, and make sure his alien school supplies don't take over the classroom! Can Albert make it through his first day without causing any chaos?

After narrowly escaping the throes of two terrible demons, Chito is soon haunted by "La Carreta Sin Bueyes" (The Creaky Wagon) and enchanted by "La Segua" (The Horse Lady), who lures him in with her mysterious beauty.
name: Chapter 3

description: As the evil karmies invade the comiXology headquarters the fearless intern seeks out the company's Executive for advise on how to eradicate the evil plague. Through flashbacks revisiting the inception of digital comics the intern gains insight into how good can overtake evil and how to save ComiXology as we know it today.
name: Getting to the Root of the Karmies, ComiXologists

description:
Dance in the Vampire Bund: The Memories of Sledge Hammer is a three-volume interlude between Dance in the Vampire Bund's first fourteen volume story arc and the upcoming second part of the series, which will launch in 2014. The Memories of Sledge Hammer delves into the past to look at the doomed love affair of one of the Vampire Bund's most deadly operatives.

Three months have passed since Princess Mina, queen of all vampires, has recaptured the Bund. The damage inflicted to vampire/human relations runs deep, but a peaceful postwar restoration is now underway.

Yet appearances can be deceiving. Somebody is trying to kill government liaison Reiko Gotoh, but her lycanthrope bodyguard, Seiji Hama, is nowhere to be found. The mystery of Hama's whereabouts can only be solved by examining the past, when the ill-fated couple first met. The past may be the key to saving Gotoh in the present-and to the future of the Vampire Bund itself!

Note: The digital edition (3/19/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: Dance in the Vampire Bund: The Memories of Sledgehammer

description: Three friends from the streets of New York reunite when one of their friends is mysteriously murdered by an ex-superhero. Jonathan Diesel, millionaire and bounty hunter, is contracted by the government to track down the killer. As events unfold, Diesel discovers the killer is not only his former hero, but also his uncle.

Digested #2 is the second in a series of short form sequential art by acclaimed Melbourne-based cartoonist Bobby.N.

Issue #2 continues the intriguing 'Oxygen' storyline from the first issue and continues his insightful vignettes with six more 'Shorts'.

In this climactic last installment of the newest arc of Fracture, the city of Triton is held hostage by the Society of Thorns and its minions, while Virtue fights Jeff for control of their shared existence. An unexpected ally joins the battle with disastrous consequences, leading to a final shocking twist. Variant cover by Steve Bryant!

Note: The digital edition (3/19/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Ghost cop Tom Fraley stands alone, his allies fallen like so many dominoes, while the serial killer who took Tom's earthly life 65 years ago becomes ever more powerful as he claims more victims. Can Tom put a stop to the rampage before the killer becomes truly omnipotent?

Gina brings her little niece Tifanny along to be data coordinator on a low-key class trip to Civ Alpha. Despite safety precautions, she wants someone to help protect Tif'. Gina's newest pupil, Ayane "Mistress" Anno, is all too eager to volunteer, but the cute-obsessed wrestler's fear-inducing eyes don't foster much trust in her charge. When Tif' manages to trip a deadly trap, though, she'll either have to trust Ayane enough to be rescued, or face destruction at... her own hands?

Note: The digital edition (3/19/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

The repercussions of "the healing" come home. Retirement villages are forcing now healthy elderly residents out of their rooms and back with their families. And not every family or resident is ready for the sudden change. Meanwhile, Donna Gibbs (President of Vanness-Headley Corporation's Pharmatherapeutics R&D division) is having problems with her new assistant, Anthony, as he starts to doubt Donna's reasons for investigating "the healing."

This is it! At last Zakk Ridley comes face to face with galactic president, Travis Beckham, and things really go off with a bang! Don't miss the conclusion of this thrill-a-minute sci-fi spectacular! It'll blow your space-socks off!

volume.name: The Intergalactic Adventures of Zakk Ridley

description:
When everyone at Riverdale High is fascinated by an online gossip site written by someone under the moniker the "WHISPERER," Kevin makes it his mission to unmask the writer who is spreading rumors about his fellow students. But when he finds himself the center of an ugly gossip piece, he ups his game to solve the mystery of the secret gossiper. Can he find out who the rumor-spreader is and save the day (and everyone's reputations) or will the Whisperer live on? Find out in "Elementary, My Dear Kevin!" a fun, Sherlock Holmes-style spoof!

Note: The digital edition (3/19/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Elementary My Dear Kevin!

description: The monstrous human being called Agent Lowenstein has escaped from his government holding cell. Or was he released? Regardless, the body count is rising as he makes his way out of the desert and into the city, heading straight for Spencer Cradle, aka the government's super-smart cleanup agent the Davidian. Meanwhile, John Knowledge puts his endgame into motion...
name: Part Three: Somewhere in the World it's Midnight

description: From the Shuster award winning creators of Least I Could Do and Gutters comes a loving nod to classic fantasy novels that manages to flip the genre on it's head. Unlikely heros cut a swath through a fantasy world that is extremely familiar and yet very different. A naive elven hunter makes an strange friend in an undead warlock and the two manage to make both enemies and friends as they fight the good fight against the Legaran Empire.

Seeking Samarkand Part 3 of 8

Escaping from Akkades was just the tip of the iceberg as things spiral fast for the Lost Kids and trouble seems to be in every corner.

After barely making it out with their lives, they now find themselves in a creepy forest... at night... with nothing but a torch...

Not much to fear... right?

Darreon has killed all the major heroes and super-mercenaries. Now Lucky Dawg Incorporated is being sent to New Llello. What chance does a team that barely knows each other have against a demi-god that can kill with the snap of his fingers?

Home Invasion

In part three of MAKESHIFT MIRACLE, Colby and Iris must try to unravel the mystery of her appearance -- and the strange powers she has started to manifest!
name: Chapter 9: Where Dreams Go

volume.name: Makeshift Miracle: The Girl From Nowhere

description:
No Such Thing As a Free Lunch

The Rouran Academy sports festival is coming up, and Sakamachi Kinjiro has a lot riding on one very special event...but there's one small problem. How do you prepare for a competition when your challenger won't tell you what it is? Narumi Schrödinger, one of the school's top athletes, has plans to make Jiro pay for going on a date with her little sister. The event she has in store for him will cost him dearly!

Of course, that's the least of Jiro's troubles. After suddenly losing their home in a fire, he and his sister, Kureha, have to look for a new place to live. Suzutsuki Kanade offers a helping hand...but the price may be more than Jiro can handle.

Note: The digital edition (3/19/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 23: Sports Festival Scramble
  • Chapter 24: Versus Complex
  • Chapter 25: Working For the Suzutsukis Isn't Working For Me
  • Chapter 26: Isn't That Love?
  • Chapter 27: An Unexpected Rebirth
name: Vol. 5

description:
The world of MEGA MAN X returns! Blast from the deadly jungle to the ferocious future in the Mega Man issue everyone is talking about! "Shadow of the Moon" Part Two: Mega Man leads his fellow robots into the mysterious ruins of the Temple of the Moon. What horrors will they uncover hidden in the shadows? MEANWHILE, halfway around the world, Break Man finally confronts Tempo! Then, in "The X Factor" Part Two -- Maverick incidents are on the rise! Dr. Cain organizes the Hunters, but will X stand for their violent ways? Find out in this stunning story featuring all new cover and interior art by PATRICK "SPAZ" SPAZIANTE!

Note: The digital edition (3/19/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Shadow of Ra Moon Part Two: Feat Itself; The X-Factor Part 2

description:
Field Trip

Vampire kings, fire dogs, and the queen of Canada-it's a rough day for Sergio. Meanwhile, Jet's locked up and Quinton, as well as a creepy scientist and some giant haired twin girls, seem unhappy about it. Will Quinton finally do something?

The world is falling apart! Caught in a burning city between an army and monstrous Demons, Seren can only try to escape the destruction. And high in the mountains, the rest of our heroes are on the trail of something dark and mysterious that may be even worse...

Beasts of Montreal

The feature story in this Vol. is Honolulu Lorie's Lava Love Lounge and Poodle Emporium!

Seven pages inspired by the rhythms and themes of the great Tom Waits, whom I've long admired. And some scumbags, old friends I knew from Toronto but mostly from and still in Windsor Ont.

Early draft was scrawled on napkins and band flyers in various bars in the '90s while Waits' music filled my ears.

Also found within, illustrations, a cut scene from my graphic novel Dream Life, and a pair of images created for Occupy Comics.

Some old Comic Jam pages in back, along with an article about my personal history with Jams.

The Shadow's agents help break a man out of jail in order to get some more information on what Shiwan Khan is chasing-only problem is that the ancient foe and CEO of Nissteco is not the only one! Meanwhile, religious figureheads get nervous as the 'Light' gains more and more popularity-coming to the conclusion that something has to be done before everything gets out of hand.
name: Shadows and Light Part 4: Balance of Power

description: Sylvia and Carlos find more than what they bargained for while investigating the jungles of The Ten

"OUTBREAK"

Slacker genius Dr. David Loren used to worry about the deadly consequences of his creations from the safety of his laboratory... but not anymore! Deployed to Taiwan to oversee a field test gone awry, will having a SEAL Team as his bodyguards be enough to ensure that David returns home outside of a body bag?

Collects THINK TANK #9-12.

Note: The digital edition (3/19/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Outbreak

description: Will Sama find the Sugar Stone, or will the Cloud prevent him from finding what his father needs? The Undertown saga continues.
name: Vol. 2

description: The legendary Beast is a surefire way to scare the new kids at summer camp. But when the line between prank and myth blurs, camp counselors Jeremy and April investigate exactly who is responsible for terrorizing kids in the dead of night—if it’s a WHO at all.
name: Beast of Blue Mountain Part 1 of 2

description:
Part two of The Legend of the Ghost Pony continues in this terrifyingly sweet installment from Hasbro designer/illustrator of My Little Pony, Gayle Middleton!

Ghost Ponies have been the harbingers of the weird for years. Whenever they appear, creatures near have disappeared, never to return. Where do they come from? What is their terrible secret?

And what is the Ghost Pony's connection to a vampyre baby named Lily Rose Shadowlyn? Find out in this all new adventure!
name: Legend of the Ghost Pony

description: Night Moves focuses on a dark world, a secret world, in which our intrepid hero is in way over her head. As the darkness begins to spread around her entire life, she is desperate to get answers about what is really going on in her town. Fear the night in this terrifying tale of monsters and mayhem.

volume.name: Vincent Price Presents Black and White

description: During the 1960's, Grant Worth's ability to control machines made him a legendary figure in Detroit. But when Worth's powers become obsolete because of society's own progress, he is forced to discover what happens when a superhero can no longer be super...
name: Chapter III

description:
Experience a new kind of Iron Fist story, steeped in legends and fables stretching back through the centuries!

Orphaned as a child and raised in the lost city of K'un Lun, Danny Rand returned to America as the mystical martial artist Iron Fist-- but all his kung-fu skills can't help him find his place in the modern world. After learning the legacy of the Iron Fist holds more secrets than he ever dreamed, Danny is invited to fight in a tournament against the Immortal Weapons. At stake is the life of his friend, the legacy of his father and mentor-- and the future of K'un Lun!

Collecting Immortal Iron Fist #1-16 and Annual #1, Immortal Iron Fist: Orson Randall and the Green Mist of Death #1, and material from Immortal Iron Fist: The Origin of Danny Rand and Civil War: Choosing Sides #1-- written by Ed Brubaker and Matt Fraction; and illustrated by David Aja, Travel Foreman, Russ Heath, Khari Evans, Kano, Tonci Zonjic, Daniel Brereton, Howard Chaykin, Jelena Kevic Djurdjevic, Nick Dragotta, Lewis Larosa, Mitch Breitweiser and more.
name: Vol. 1

The Seven Capital Cities of Heaven

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: The Seven Capital Cities of Heaven
The Book of the Iron Fist

object_credits.name: The Book of the Iron Fist

description:
Torajirou and Sakura have survived their lousy childhoods by watching each other's backs. When Sakura finds himself at the mercy of a yakuza gang, Tora has to do what he can to save his best friend. Will he be able to win back Sakura's freedom, or has Tora bitten off more than he can chew?

Contents

  • Prologue
  • Chapter 1: Dawn of Life
  • Chapter 2: Student Life
  • Postscript
name: Vol. 1

description: What kind of whack job would put on a mask and a skin-tight suit and head out into the city after midnight? I mean, what is this guy really up to? What pathology, what perverse proclivity are we dealing with here? Is he fighting crime? Of course not, he's just going clubbing-and he's frankly perplexed when the aggressive bar flies & drunks single him out. The guy in question is Manx, a costumed cat man. Rich but unfulfilled, Manx goes to Dr. Grippo, a sultry lady shrink from Eastern Europe, to figure out his life. All hell breaks loose when Manx reveals to the amorous Dr. Grippo that he has fallen for Delia, a hottie he picks up on one of his late night excursions. Romance! Violence! Weed! Adventure! Alcohol! Twists! All these things abound in Lafler's charming Cat Suit.

The world famous scientist and explorer Kurt Dunder gets an unexpected visit one evening by the ill-reputed author of dubious traveller's books, Jorgen Birk, who has an amazing story to tell.

Jorgen Birk has found the long lost notes and maps of David Livingstone's last Africa expedition in 1871. And they bear evidence of the existence of the legendary Polo people, a mongoloid race of giants, that were once believed to live deep inside the jungles of darkest Africa.

Kurt Dunder does not believe in such romantic nonsense, but when Birk is kidnapped, Dunder has to revise his views. Perhaps the map of Livingstone was right after all?

Assisted by his friend Bill Milton and Birk's chimpanzee Attila, Kurt embarks a journey into the jungle of Congo in a search for the elusive Polo people. But they are not the only ones looking for the secret - and the treasure. Soon the hunters are the hunted!

This is the first book in the KURT DUNDER series.
name: Kurt Dunder In Africa

description:
Undermanned and under-funded, the Filipino Heroes League does what it can to fight against injustice.

It's tough being a superhero but it's even tougher being a third-world superhero.
name: Sticks and Stones

description:
Please Sorry Mercy God

The mysterious city known as "the Bowl" has only come to expect bad things from William "Bill" Memphis, but when he stumbles upon a young lady in distress, the balding triggerman alters the path he has been given by choosing righteous rage before villainous duty.
name: Please Sorry Mercy God

description:
Shady Ranch

An off-duty FBI Agent and his family become stranded in the California desert when low altitude nuclear bomb is detonated in the atmosphere. Things go from bad to worse as the Electro-Magnetic pulse from the blast fries their car and cell phones.
name: Shady Ranch

description: Today. At the Eiffel Tower, the Guardian of the Republic frees innocent visitors taken hostage by the notorious criminal cartel, CRIMEN. Then, with the help of the fearsome super-hero John Mist, and of Alima, a young girl he met during the confrontation, he tries to stop Baroud, the leader of Crimen, from achieving his mysterious goals at the Louvre Museum...
name: Enter: The New Marianne

description: Helper Bot is tasked with delivering a mindfile to Bostrom Technologies while avoiding the hazards of Robot City.
When a mad scientist releases his monstrous creations on the city, his hapless lab assistant must convince him to save the day! And what better way to do that than unleash even more monsters?!?
A collection of three short stories about war.

Growing up in a single parent household with an abusive father, Sora always took comfort in knowing that his best friend and neighbor Tetsuya is always there for him. Their relationship has always been a close one, but when they realize they're beginning to develop feelings for each other beyond the boundaries of "best friends", Tetsuya starts to avoid Sora all together. Will they be able to regain the comfortable friendship they once shared? Or will it all fall apart?
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: A Night of A Thousand Nights

description: He imagined realms of wizards, orcs, and hobbits and elevated fantasy from pulp to respected literature. J.R.R. Tolkien, the iconic author who captivated generations with his rich and complex mythology of Middle Earth, is the subject of his own tale in a special edition of Bluewater Productions' latest biography comic title "Orbit." This edition is translated in spanish!

volume.name: Orbit: JRR Tolkien - The True Lord of the Rings

description:
Can Chris Christie navigate the often treacherous waters of presidential politics and remain New Jersey's favorite son? Read the story of Christie's rise to power, the formation of his political platform, and his devotion to his home state. New Jersey, and the country, are watching.

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location
ACover AMichael Kasinger
BCover BJayfri Hashim

Holding Out For a Hero

FabMan, sick of being treated as a joke and seeing no representation for the LGBTQ in a world full of heroes, assembles the greatest super powered LGBTQ heroes from around the world to form The Pride!

Who joins? And what nefarious shadow is building just out of sight? Will The Pride be up for the task?

Get in on the ground floor today!

Blu and Jewel, the last known surviving Blue Spix Macaws, are having a great time raising their children in the safety of the Blu Bird Sanctuary, but there may be trouble in paradise! When Blu overhears Tulio and Linda talking about their money troubles, Blu takes it upon himself to save the sanctuary and his friends' livelihood - if only he could think of a way. When bulldog Luiz tells Blu about a legendary elixir hidden somewhere in the jungle, Blu thinks that could be the answer. That is, of course, if cockatoo Nigel doesn't get there first, and if they can make it past the villainous snaky Ssssssalbatore in one piece!

The next chapter in the epic story of Rio begins right here!

Note: The digital edition (3/19/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Snakes Alive!

description:
The Trap: Chapter One

Two runaway teens break into a decaying home in search of abandoned valuables, only to be ripped apart by a dark creature.

Three months later, Marc Franco arrives back in the small town after his father's untimely death. Forced to save the family plumbing business, Marc steps into his father's place and takes his first job with the company, inspecting the old Thomas House.

When Marc arrives with his co-worker, Gabriel Ruiz, they meet up with a small construction crew and the town's main phone-line technician.

Once inside the home, plates of steel cover the windows and doors, locking them inside.
name: The Trap Chapter One

description: First volume in the acclaimed series from Don Lomax, a Vietnam veteran, that was nominated for a Harvey Award. Vietnam Journal looks at the Vietnam War through the eyes of a war journalist nicknamed 'Journal' as he chronicles the lives and events of soldiers on the front line during the Vietnam War.
name: Volume One

description: NASA astronaut Nick Thaler discovers a mysterious artifact on Mars, which exploded upon contact. Back on Earth, Nick discovers his body is now hosting a powerful alien known as Starlock...
name: The Coming of Starlock

description: Desperate to return to his far-flung homeworld, Starlock embarks on a journey that causes chaos and destruction. Pursued by the US army, will the powerful alien find refuge somewhere?
name: Countdown to Destruction

description: The evil organization S.P.I.D.E.R. takes an interest in Starlock, in whom they see the key to becoming masters of Earth. But can they force the powerful alien to do their bidding?
name: Pawn of S.P.I.D.E.R.

description: Trapped in the Soviet Union, Starlock is confronted to the Russian Super-Soldier project. Also in this issue: the alien origins of Starlock and the reasons for his imprisonment on Mars!
name: Behind the Iron Curtain
